    {
      "id": "sybil_2_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_2",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sorted 2004 BMW M3 (E46) finished in Carbon Black. At its heart is the S54 3.2L naturally aspirated inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and a high-pressure VANOS system that has been recently overhauled for optimal cam timing. This example features the sought-after 6-speed longitudinal manual transmission paired with a factory-spec limited-slip differential. Crucially, the rear subframe mounting points have been reinforced to ensure structural integrity under high torque loads. The suspension has been upgraded with Bilstein B16 coilovers, enhancing the MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear geometry for sharper turn-in and reduced body roll. While the exterior shows minor road wear consistent with a driver\u2019s car, the drivetrain and chassis remain tight, providing the visceral, high-revving performance characteristic of this analog era.",
      "price": 31500.0,
      "reputation": 0.4,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_10_listing_3",
