      "timestep_posted": 30
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_7",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Offered is a mechanically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera (996.2) featuring the 3.6L naturally aspirated flat-six engine equipped with VarioCam Plus. This unit delivers linear power through a 6-speed manual Getrag gearbox to the rear wheels. Crucially, the IMS bearing has been updated with an LN Engineering retrofit, and the rear main seal (RMS) was replaced during the same service interval. The suspension geometry remains tight, utilizing the original MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear setup for superior turn-in precision. Deceleration is managed by four-piston aluminum monobloc calipers. While the exterior shows honest road wear consistent with a well-loved driver, the powertrain remains robust and the throttle calibration is exceptionally crisp. A performance-first example for the true enthusiast.",
